<manpage>
    <sample url="sdk\operating_system\crt\libc\math\atan">atan</sample>
    <title> atan, atan2</title>
    <volume>C Run-Time Library Functions</volume>
    <routine_idx> math_idx.htm </routine_idx>

    <description>
        <para>The atan function computes the principal value of the arctangent of x.</para>
    </description>

    <syntax>
        <return_val>double</return_val>
        <func_name>atan</func_name>
        <parameters>
            <func_param>
                <param_type>double</param_type>
                <param_name>x</param_name>
                <param_note>
                    <para>Any double precision numbers.</para>
                </param_note>
            </func_param>
        </parameters>
    </syntax>
    <syntax>
        <return_val>double</return_val>
        <func_name>atan2</func_name>
        <parameters>
            <func_param>
                <param_type>double</param_type>
                <param_name>y</param_name>
                <param_note>
                    <para>Any double precision numbers.</para>
                </param_note>
            </func_param>
            <func_param>
                <param_type>double</param_type>
                <param_name>x</param_name>
            </func_param>
        </parameters>
    </syntax>

    <return>
        <para>atan returns the arctangent of x. atan2 returns the arctangent of y/x.</para>
    </return>

    <remarks>
        <para>The atan function calculates the arctangent of x. atan2 calculates the arctangent of y/x. atan2 is well defined for every point other than the origin, even if x equals 0 and y does not equal to 0.</para>
    </remarks>

    <requirements>
        <routine>
            <routine_name>atan</routine_name>
            <headerfile>math.h</headerfile>
            <compatibility>ANSI, Windows 2000, Elastos 2.0</compatibility>
        </routine>
    </requirements>

    <example>
<pre>
//==========================================================================
// Copyright (c) 2000-2004,  Elastos, Inc.  All Rights Reserved.
//==========================================================================

/* atan.cpp: This program uses atan to calculates the arctangent.
 */

#include &lt;math.h&gt;
#include &lt;stdio.h&gt;

int main()
{
    double x, y;

    x = -862.4200;
    y = atan(x);
    printf(&quot;Arctangent of %f: %f\n&quot;, x, y);

    return 0;
}
</pre>
    </example>
<result>
Arctangent of -862.420000: -1.569637
</result>



